reviewText:
Great game!

-Classic RPG-Maker style with a lot of things to do ( Smithing, Alchemy, Fishing... A lot more! );
-Each one of the principal skills have a leveling system, so be prepared to spend some time on cities;
-Battle system remember a lot Final Fantasy 5. The monsters are not that cool-looking, but dont look that bad too;
-Your enemies level up, just like you. So, dont expect to have an easy time when fighting;
-Some Harvest Moon features, like planting, milk cows, gather eggs from chickens, have a family;
-Dont finished the game yet, but, so far, the history is good and the characters (there is a lot of them) are Intriguing and funny ( especialy that zombie ).

Really worth the price for such a good game with so many things to do!
